> I'm also fine with adding additional architecture support to the tooling (like push-manifest.sh and the linuxkit tool) later, to allow others building LinuxKit images for other architectures.
> 
> However, adding a new supported architecture, ie something the LinuxKit project would provide images for, update the kernels etc is something we would have to consider very carefully and it would require access to suitable build infrastructure etc.

We probably should have something in the docs about:

* how to build for a new architecture (requirements, process, etc.)
* requirements for a fully supported architecture

